Here's the pattern for reading a number from the console:

```csharp
Console.Write("Enter a number: ");
string input = Console.ReadLine();
double number = double.Parse(input);
```

You'll need to do this twice — once for each number.

Division by zero will cause an error. You should check for this before performing the division:

```csharp
if (num2 == 0)
{
    Console.WriteLine("Error: Cannot divide by zero!");
}
else
{
    double result = num1 / num2;
    Console.WriteLine($"Result: {num1} / {num2} = {result}");
}
```

This pattern of checking for errors before they happen is called **defensive programming**.

